 The Nigerian Senate has confirmed the appointment of Muhammad Nami as Executive Chairman of the Federal Inland Revenue Service. Nami replaces Babatunde Fowler. Announcing Nami’s confirmation, the FIRS in a post on Twitter, said, “The Senate a few minutes ago confirmed the appointment of Muhammad Nami as Executive Chairman, Federal Inland Revenue Service. “Senate President, Ahmed Lawan, slammed his gavel at 2:51pm today (Wednesday), signalling the confirmation of Nami’s appointment.” 